GoalTribe ‚Äì Final Release Notes (v1.0.0)

 Student: Mantikologa Mashamaite
 Date: 07 November 2025

---

Summary
This version upgrades the original prototype into a fully functional production-ready app.  
The improvements focus on usability, reliability, and modern Android practices.

---

  New Features Since Prototype

1. Google Single Sign-On (SSO)
- Integrated *Firebase Authentication* with Google Sign-In.
- Simplified user login with one tap.
- Added detailed logs to monitor sign-in/out actions.

 2. Offline Mode with Sync
- Added *Room Database* to store local data when offline.
- Implemented *WorkManager* to sync data automatically once online.
- Added sync progress logs for debugging and demonstration.

 3. Real-Time Notifications
- Integrated *Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)*.
- App receives live push notifications and displays them instantly.
- Notifications redirect users to related screens when tapped.

4. Multi-Language Support
- Added strings.xml for isiZulu (values-zu) and Afrikaans (values-af).
- Implemented an in-app toggle to change languages dynamically.

 5. Logging and Code Documentation
- Added Log.d, Log.i, and Log.e throughout major modules.
- Every new feature is explained with inline Kotlin comments.

---

üí° Innovative Highlights
- *Offline-first architecture*: Users can continue interacting even without data.
- *Automatic synchronization* creates a seamless experience when reconnecting.
- *Localization* makes the app inclusive for South African audiences.
- *Firebase integration* for both SSO and notifications adds modern cloud connectivity.

